Top Stories (February 20)

CALIFORNIA GOVERNOR SAYS PLAN WILL SAVE UTILITIES, KEEP RATES LOW
Gov. Gray Davis unveiled a multibillion-dollar plan Friday that he claims 
will rescue debt-ridden utilities with little or no rate increase, but the 
long-awaited proposal wasn't immediately embraced by either the Legislature 
or utility executives.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/02/20/krtbn/0000-0479-SA-UTILITY

ENERGY EAST PLANS TO BUY RGS ENERGY FOR $1.4 BLN
The Energy East Corp., which owns New York State Electric & Gas, plans to 
announce today that it agreed to acquire the RGS Energy group of Rochester, 
for $1.4 billion, The New York Times reported in its Tuesday editions.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
02/20/eng-djn/eng-djn_032111_60_2651821752079

SOUTHERN COMPANY TO ADD 6,600 MEGAWATTS GENERATING CAPACITY
Southern Co. (SO) will add an undisclosed number of power plants to boost 
generating capacity in the Southeast by 6,600 megawatts by 2004.
http://199.97.97.79/IMDS%PMADJN0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/djn/2001/
02/20/eng-djn/eng-djn_102036_32_3960820701905

NEW MEXICO LAWMAKER TOUTS BILL TO DELAY DEREGULATION
With the New Mexico Legislature nearing the halfway point of this year's 
60-day session in Santa Fe, lawmakers are engaged in a flurry of activity 
trying to meet today's deadline for introduction of all legislation.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMAKRT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/knightri
dder/2001/02/20/krtbn/0000-0016-AX-DEREGULATE-BILL

KINDER MORGAN TO BUILD 3,300 MW OF GAS-FIRED GENERATION; WILLIAMS TO MARKET 
POWER
Kinder Morgan, Inc. and a unit of Williams today announced a 16-year 
agreement under which Williams will supply fuel to and market 3,300 megawatts 
of capacity for six natural gas-fired, intermediate-peaking power generation 
facilities to be developed by Kinder Morgan Power Company over the next four 
years.
http://199.97.97.163/IMDS%PMANAT0%read%/home/content/users/imds/feeds/comtex/2
001/02/20/pr/0000-3437-tx-kinder-morgan

